post_text: This is an exciting time for everyone in the Delaware Valley region. The Philadelphia Eagles are Super Bowl Champions (Go Birds!) and tomorrow the tri-state area will celebrate the team’s well-decorated tenacity by sponsoring a parade with numbers that promise to rival the most well-attended events in the history of our area. We anticipate logistical issues, including but not limited to transportation interruptions, and therefore have decided to close school on Thursday, February 8th.
